0.title: Rules
0.body:
[b]UNO[/b]

The objective of the game is to be the first player to get rid of all the cards in their hand by matching cards with the discard pile.


[b]Set-Up[/b]

Shuffle the deck of UNO cards. Then deal 7 cards to each player by right-clicking the deck of UNO cards and clicking on Deal in the context menu. This forms each players starting hand. The remaining cards in the deck form the draw pile. Once each player has seven cards, turn the top card of the deck over and place it next to the draw pile. That card forms the discard pile. You are now ready to play UNO.


[b]How To Play[/b]

Play begins with the player who is left to the dealer and proceeds clockwise. When it is your turn, you may discard a card from your hand that matches either the color or the number/symbol of the card on the top of the discard pile. Once you've done so, your turn ends and play moves on to the next player.

If you can't play a card from your hand that matches the card on top of the discard pile, then you must draw a card from the draw pile. If the card you've drawn matches the card in the discard pile, you may play it immediately. Otherwise, your turn ends.

Sometimes you are able to play a card with a special symbol on it. These are called action cards. Once you've played an action card, it's effect takes place immediately. (See the "Action Cards" section for more details on the effects of the different actions)

If, once you've played a card, you are left with only one card in your hand, you must shout "UNO" or type "UNO" in chat. If you fail to do so and someone calls you out, you must draw two cards from the draw pile.

When a player has no cards remaining in their hand, the game ends, and that player is the winner.


[b]Action Cards[/b]

Skip - This card has a symbol that depicts a circle with a strike through it. When a player plays this card, the next player must skip his turn immediately.

Draw Two - This card has a symbol that depicts two cards. When a player plays this card plays this card, the next player must draw two cards from the draw pile. That player also skips his/her turn.

Reverse - This card has a symbol that depicts two arrows, pointing in opposite directions. When a player plays this card, the play order then flows in the reverse direction. So, if the game was being played clockwise, the game would then be played counter-clockwise (and vice-versa).

Wild - This card is black and has all four colors on it. When a player plays this card, that player must specify a color (Red, Yellow, Green or Blue). The wild card then serves as a card in the color that the player specified, and the next player must play a card in that color.

Wild Draw Four - This card is black and has a symbol that depicts 4 cards, one for each color. This card is played like the Wild card with one additional effect. After the card is played and the color is chosen, the next player must draw 4 cards from the draw pile and skip his/her turn.


Go To [url=http://unotips.org/pdf/official_rules.pdf]http://unotips.org/pdf/official_rules.pdf[/url] if you would like to read the official rules for UNO, including scoring for points.
